Sanofi Is Studying Ophthalmology Acquisitions, Les Echos Says

-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 
2011-02-14T05:31:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/sanofi-is-studying-ophthalmology-acquisitions-les-echos-says.html
  Sanofi-Aventis SA  plans to spend 1
billion euros over the next three years on acquisitions in
ophthalmology,  Les Echos  reported, without saying where it got
the information.  The company is currently studying “closely” four
potential purchases, three of which are in the U.S. and the
other in  Israel , the French newspaper said. It didn’t name the
companies.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  